---
import DefaultLayout from '@layouts/DefaultLayout.astro'
import PageHeader from '@components/PageHeader.astro'
---

<DefaultLayout title="Accessibility statement">
  <PageHeader
    title="Accessibility Statement"
    subtitle="Employ Wizard is committed to providing an accessible platform for HR professionals. Our AI-powered recruitment tool meets WCAG 2.2 AA standards to ensure usability for all users."
    bgType="bordered"
  />
  <section class="narrow container my-16">
    <div class="space-content">
      <h2>Introduction</h2>
      <p>
        This accessibility statement applies to <strong>employwizard.com</strong>. At <strong>Employ Wizard</strong>,
        we are committed to ensuring digital accessibility for HR professionals of all abilities. We believe that
        recruitment tools should be usable by everyone, regardless of physical or technological limitations.
        Accessibility is a core value in our commitment to providing an inclusive platform for talent acquisition.
      </p>

      <h2>WCAG Compliance</h2>
      <p>
        Employ Wizard is designed to conform to the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.2, Level AA. These
        guidelines ensure our platform is accessible to HR professionals with a wide array of disabilities,
        including visual, auditory, physical, speech, cognitive, language, learning, and neurological disabilities.
        Our accessible interface supports screen readers, keyboard navigation, and other assistive technologies.
      </p>

      <h2>Accessibility Features</h2>
      <p>
        Employ Wizard has been designed with accessibility as a core principle. The following accessibility features have been
        implemented to ensure our platform is usable by HR professionals with diverse abilities:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-inside list-disc">
        <li>WCAG 2.2 AA compliant interface with proper semantic HTML structure</li>
        <li>Full keyboard navigation support for all features and functions</li>
        <li>High contrast design options for users with visual impairments</li>
        <li>Screen reader compatibility with comprehensive ARIA labels and descriptions</li>
        <li>Resizable text and zoom functionality up to 200%</li>
        <li>Clear focus indicators and logical tab order throughout the platform</li>
        <li>Alternative text for all images and icons</li>
        <li>Error messages and form validation with clear, descriptive feedback</li>
        <li>Consistent navigation patterns and predictable user interface</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Continuous Improvement</h2>
      <p>
        We are committed to continuous improvement of Employ Wizard's accessibility features. Our development team regularly
        reviews user feedback and accessibility best practices to enhance the platform's usability for all HR professionals.
        We conduct quarterly accessibility audits and implement improvements based on user needs and WCAG guideline updates.
      </p>

      <h2>Report Accessibility Issues</h2>
      <p>
        We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of Employ Wizard. If you encounter any barriers or have suggestions
        for improvement, please help us by providing the following information:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-inside list-disc">
        <li><strong>Feature:</strong> The specific feature or page where you experienced the issue</li>
        <li><strong>Description:</strong> A clear description of the problem or barrier encountered</li>
        <li><strong>Browser/Assistive Technology:</strong> The browser and any assistive technology used</li>
        <li><strong>Contact details:</strong> Your name and email address (optional)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Please contact us at <strong>accessibility@employwizard.com</strong> or through our main support line at <strong>info@employwizard.com</strong>.</p>

      <h2>Technical Support</h2>
      <p>
        For HR professionals requiring additional accessibility accommodations or technical support, our team provides:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-inside list-disc">
        <li>Dedicated accessibility support hotline</li>
        <li>Custom training sessions for assistive technology users</li>
        <li>Alternative format documentation upon request</li>
        <li>Priority support for accessibility-related technical issues</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Contact Information</h2>
      <p>
        For further questions or comments regarding this accessibility statement or the accessibility of Employ Wizard,
        please contact us through our dedicated accessibility team at <strong>accessibility@employwizard.com</strong> or
        our main support line at <strong>info@employwizard.com</strong>.
      </p>

      <h2>Compliance Information</h2>
      <p>
        This accessibility statement was prepared on <strong>January 15, 2024</strong> and is reviewed quarterly to ensure
        ongoing compliance with accessibility standards. Employ Wizard undergoes regular accessibility testing against
        WCAG 2.2 AA guidelines, with our most recent comprehensive audit completed on <strong>December 2024</strong>.
        We maintain detailed accessibility conformance reports available upon request.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</DefaultLayout>
